article.description: — Jaden House had 29 points in High Point's 85-82 win against Furman on Tuesday night.
article.headline: High Point defeats Furman 85-82
article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- — Jaden House had 29 points in High Point's 85-82 win against Furman on Tuesday night. Zack Austin scored the last two points of the game with a pair of free throws with six seconds left. House added seven rebounds for the Panthers (8-1). Abdoulaye scored 21 points, going 8 of 10 (5 for 6 from distance). Austin recorded 14 points and shot 4 for 7 (3 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free-throw line. Mike Bothwell led the Paladins (6-3) in scoring, finishing with 29 points and seven rebounds. Garrett Hien added 15 points for Furman. JP Pegues also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
